The sign says Havath lives here, and considering you don't know who that is, you decide to not enter.

You\..\..\.. knock on the wood near the door, and Vivian eagerly becons you inside. It seems like this tree was mostly hollowed out, at least at this level, to be turned into a home. You are surprised to see a staircase leading to a second level, how much room do these trees have? Still, it is a house inside of a tree, so it's a fairly cozy space, this floor seems to be both the living room and the kitchen.

This leads to the main section of the Elven village, which contains much of the more mundane housing, as well as the bathhouse and pillory. The only thing you have a reason to visit out of those in the bathhouse, if you are interested.
